[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying access modifiers**\n\nI'm thinking about the implications of having a package-private target class vs. public implementations in a public API. If `getConstructor` works for a package-private class, that raises questions because it usually checks if the member is public and the declaring class must be public. For methods, `getMethod` will return only public methods from public classes. So, if a class isn't public, a public method can exist, but the class itself may not be accessible.\n\n**Evaluating class structure**\n\nI'm considering whether nested public static helpers with private or public constructors in the same public test class could be idiomatic. Sure, it creates `$` in the helper class names, but that seems acceptable. However, I wonder if dynamic class loading of these classes requires additional metadata. I'm thinking nested helper classes inside tests are common, as they're fewer than top-level, but maybe a package-private class with a public constructor isn't an issue.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07ed28c32efde3390169f8ec2d96cc81a397d5fc4e588e52d5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-Ow-pTTn-6Z329VBSF362705OQYL5qPOUQC1FtG997vxLUZeJmgUjF41tnUtHSxdQokLR7EjH8ro5ej3UWOBu4hZC1-NAoEHxK7vco1mj2ftKs9BJPXj9CfqQKziTgHfGQJDKAjPAyN5EKTApsgdJ60_JeDSU-HHcrHBEzHDQiSDYvyLdpOclJDzozirbA6mwseOew6XaJn8xsMJh05jfO3ZPT_ZbYtcJDfFjfkcXjj5AclZUHjOCblTPkLMxgGggwZCbLITPVF9YOaVRsc6NQa-S3SYaf6mtkpwOG-fi1mDw7jvdQZocDSBy7fc_4IGO2VA5OhR02bRa-nBd1ndwVN6RDrGersbMoiwSO0puFANGkmOJYaeqCYEry9rhbxJXmO3IghOJJoasm46bhrNTCvKvB2cAky7kg_ZqqDQ2aJrT2awpg3nMQ5QDDx-Vpzaq0vM0hOfo_C7fKtWs1VSIinKrsJsdqXK4Yt7nQDFVe-xb_ugeQioNIRDKX0oqry1tGSuI5BdlW1sB74GsHyk0HmUk2PgFR2HHliH3FnwuBLq1HS9rzTt7IKiOo3vpbJqWHPe53NOyvwDiPXHWnEZv-BaTBdBoRih3IkYDJt782Fz8R7Ykhp26gmLUSffq8YSn_4bOK_f4VYz-w6kdHAWE2fdc05mtkDn9Utghf5-6MzwDpafUb2CCbYvZfEnMCGLmGeQUFXh46zsli39wo-iQAwVJTQ2GusK5